Jeffersonville Elementary School
August 16 at 12:00 PM ·

The Faculty and Staff of Jeffersonville Elementary School would like to welcome our students back for the 2020 – 2021 school year. We want to take this opportunity to thank our parents for choosing our school and entrusting us with your scholar's educational needs. You are a vital piece of the puzzle, and we appreciate your role and impact you make for every scholar's success. The success of our school is dependent on the working relationship between all stakeholders of Twiggs County. Our number one priority will be to work together to provide every student with the educational opportunities needed to succeed. Join us in our journey toward academic success. Our students deserve the best.

We are currently in a time that none of us have ever experienced and a lot of us may feel lost right now. Twiggs County Public Schools have been working tirelessly and weighing decisions that need to be made to help keep everyone safe and fight against COVID-19.

Our job is to make sure that the students of TCPS get their education and opportunity. But we also want to make sure that we keep them safe in order to get a chance.

*** Please tune in to tonight's Board Meeting, going live at 6:00 P.M. ***

Jacquez "Rell" Harris: Twiggs District 3 Board of Education Representative
June 19 at 9:05 AM ·

Good Morning,

Superintendent Elgin Dixon, Assistant Superintendent Tyron Bacon, Ms. Tina Thames, Mrs. Elizabeth Ricks, Mr. Jonathan King, Dr. Linda Ramsey, and to all of our amazing faculty and staff of the Twiggs County School District, Job Well Done!!!
Graduation on last evening was nothing short of a first class production. While the world is in a global pandemic we celebrated our future on yesterday with an amazing ceremony that exemplified pride, dignity, cobra spirit, but most of all student achievement! To the technology, maintenance, and custodial departments, Thank You for all that you do behind the scenes!
To our parents, stakeholders, and graduates, you looked amazing while maintaining the integrity of a true graduation ceremony. Thank you!
Congratulations Twiggs County Comprehensive Middle-High School Class of 2020!

“Together We Are Better.”

Jacquez J. Harris
District 3 BOE
🦉📚🍎

shared_text:
Twiggs County Sheriffs Office
May 19 at 8:34 PM ·

Attention Seniors

I would like to take a moment to congratulate the young men and women of the graduating classes of Twiggs County High School and Twiggs Academy. Through your hard work and perseverance, you have earned your high school diploma and reached one of the most important milestones of your lives.

I know many of you maybe apprehensive of what the future holds, but I would encourage you to look to that future with a determination of success and continue to persevere. Chase your dreams and know that you can catch them. Learn from those who have gone before you and be a mentor and an inspiration to those who will come behind.

I wish each of you success in your future endeavors and I pray the Lord will guide your steps and pour out His blessing upon you.

Sincerely yours,
Sheriff Darren Mitchum

Jeffersonville Elementary School
March 25 at 11:29 AM ·

A change has happened and we all must adjust. Staying home for a while might have been fun at first, but many of you may have started to feel a little bored. Do you want to go on an adventure? Visit a place you've never been before? We've got the answer. Read a book! Books take you wherever you want to go. We have refilled the Little Free Libraries across the county. Check them out! Get a book. Read a book. Return a book. No cards. No late fees.

If there aren't any near you and you'd like to be a steward (volunteer a space in your yard and watch over it), please let us know.

Jeffersonville Elementary School
March 20 at 12:03 PM ·

Happy Friday!

We have successfully completed our first week of meal delivery. Despite a few kinks, we almost double the total number of meals delivered today. We appreciate your patience as we aim to serve Every Child. Every Day. While we are closed, please use the following service: www.foodfinder.us

You can download the APP or plug in your Zip Code to find the nearest food sources. Continue to be safe and practice the 5 precautions:
1. HANDS Wash them often
2. COUGH Into tissue & toss
3.FACE Don’t touch it
4. FEET Stay more than 3ft apart
5. FEEL sick? Stay home

Thank you to all the staff!!

Jeffersonville Elementary School
March 16 at 6:25 PM ·

Upon careful consideration and discussions with local and state partners, Twiggs County Public Schools will follow the advisement of Governor Brian Kemp and State Superintendent, Richard Woods, by closing our schools from March 17-31, 2020.

There are no identified cases of COVID-19 in the central Georgia area, but we are taking all precautions to protect our students and staff.

Effective Tuesday, March 17, 2020, all schools and facilities will be closed. All medication must be picked up by Tuesday at 4:00 PM by a parent or guardian from Central Office (952 Main Street).
text:
Jeffersonville Elementary School
March 16 at 6:25 PM ·

Upon careful consideration and discussions with local and state partners, Twiggs County Public Schools will follow the advisement of Governor Brian Kemp and State Superintendent, Richard Woods, by closing our schools from March 17-31, 2020.

There are no identified cases of COVID-19 in the central Georgia area, but we are taking all precautions to protect our students and staff.

Effective Tuesday, March 17, 2020, all schools and facilities will be closed. All medication must be picked up by Tuesday at 4:00 PM by a parent or guardian from Central Office (952 Main Street).

post_text: Twiggs County Public School District will remain open until further notice. Classes will resume as normal on Monday, March 16th. According to a statement from Superintendent Elgin Dixon, the Twiggs County Board of Education will meet Monday, March 16th in a called session to make a decision regarding future school closings. Superintendent Dixon further stated, “from an abundance of caution, all extracurricular activities and school events are cancelled until further notice. We appreciate the support of our board and stakeholders as we navigate the best course of action for our scholars and staff.”

Superintendent Dixon further stated, “from an abundance of caution, all extracurricular activities and school events are cancelled until further notice. We appreciate the support of our board and stakeholders as we navigate the best course of action for our scholars and staff.”

Congratulations to Miss Kyla Stephens! Kyla is a Senior, honor student at Twiggs County High School who is also CNA certified, a pageant winner, cheerleader and wonderful young lady!
Kyla was nominated by her Senior Advisor and teacher, Ms TaQuila Thomas, to be the “Be Strong Ambassador” at TCHS! Kyla was presented with a certificate, monogrammed duffel tote, with Adidas items, school supplies etc . Kyla has and will continue to host events to combat bullying and embrace diversity. This is the main purpose of Be Strong.
She plans to attend The University of West Georgia in the Fall. ( My friends who went there, please let me know how you can support her in this endeavor. I won’t identify you yet.😁)
Please congratulate Kyla on her award!!

shared_text:
Twiggs County High School
March 11 at 11:42 PM ·

Twiggs Co. HS track team took part in a meet that was hosted by Washington Co. on 3/10/20. It was our first scheduled meet, I'm pleased with the effort displayed but also eager to get back to work. This meet gave us a chance to compete as well as get our numbers so that we can set future goals. Makayla Davis and Zarek Burney participated in the field events: Shot put. Nadia James, Jeremy Curtis, Malik Dupont, Cheyenne Warner, Makayla Foster, and Antonious Burney competed in sprints: (100m, 200m, & 400m) Jeremy placed second in the 100m sprint with a finishing unofficial time of 11.4, Makayla Foster also displayed a strong finish in her 100m sprint. Malik had a strong finish in the 200m sprint, and expectations are high. Antonius and Cheyenne both competed in the 400m race and did well, displaying great potential for the future meets. I ask that you all help Coach Moore in congratulating your Cobras and that you help in encouraging them to continue to push and improve.

shared_text:
TaQuila Thomas is with JacQuez J LuxeLife and 2 others.
February 27 at 7:23 AM ·

My students and I went on our tour of Helms College (Macon), ate lunch at Edgar’s Bistro (culinary students from Helms operate it) and shopped at Goodwill. Edgar Helms was a visionary for starting this dynasty.👏🏽👏🏽
We were assisted by Mr Michael Wilson, who is a Wildcat😀💙💛 and friend, and will make a guest speaker/chef appearance in my class. (I have had many guests throughout the years; I always welcome more! )
One of the best parts of the visit was seeing my former FCS , ServSafe certified, EOPA , 2019 TCHS graduate: Jamontae Montae Vail! He is a culinary student at Helm’s.😀❤️👏🏽🎉 (He does accept donations, grants, scholarships etc. Please support this young man who may be your next Marcus Samuelson or Chef Roble’ etc).
*Bonus: Mr. Rouse came out of retirement to drive us!❤️😀

post_text: JEFFERSONVILLE, GA – Twiggs County Public Schools will be closed Friday, February 21, 2019. Based on the current weather advisory, hazardous road conditions, and closures, district administrators have determined, upon the recommendation of the Twiggs County Emergency Management Agency (EMA), that it is unsafe to transport students. All after school activities will be canceled. Full-time staff will report at 8:00 AM. Please continue to monitor local news outlets, district websites, and social media for further information.
